snippet.title: PASTA | Prawn Masala Pasta Recipe Cooking in Village | Spirali Pasta Recipe | Seafood Recipe
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we cooked a spirali pasta recipe using fresh prawns and colorful, healthy vegetables. We first half-cooked the pasta, then added it to a hot, big pan along with the prawns. We also added hand-ground masala for traditional taste and healthy, colorful vegetables to make this pasta both nutritious and tasty.

Finally, we enjoyed the dish in the evening at our farm. The taste was spicy and delicious!

id.title: PASTA | Resep Pasta Masala Udang Masak di Desa | Resep Pasta Spirali | Resep Makanan Laut
id.description:
Hari ini di desa kami, kami memasak resep pasta spirali menggunakan udang segar dan sayuran berwarna-warni yang menyehatkan. Pertama-tama kami memasak pasta setengah matang, lalu memasukkannya ke dalam wajan besar yang panas bersama udang. Kami juga menambahkan masala yang digiling dengan tangan untuk cita rasa tradisional dan sayuran berwarna-warni yang menyehatkan agar pasta ini bergizi dan lezat.

Akhirnya, kami menikmati hidangan ini di malam hari di pertanian kami. Rasanya pedas dan lezat!

nl-NL.title: PASTA | Garnalen Masala Pasta Recept Koken in Dorp | Spirali Pasta Recept | Zeevruchten Recept
nl-NL.description:
Vandaag kookten we in ons dorp een recept voor spirali pasta met verse garnalen en kleurrijke, gezonde groenten. Tot slot hebben we 's avonds op onze boerderij van het gerecht genoten. Het was pittig en heerlijk!

snippet.description:

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun.

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Sirens rang out in central and northern Israel as a fresh salvo of Iranian missiles was detected by the Israeli military. Iran had warned of consequences if US attacked its nuclear facilities. About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Dil Thaam Ke | Maalik | Rajkummar Rao, Huma Qureshi | Sachin-Jigar | Rashmeet K, Rana M, Amitabh B
snippet.description:
Feel the rhythm take over with Dil Thaam Ke ‚Äî the ultimate dance Song from Maalik! Starring Rajkummar Rao and Huma Qureshi, this high-energy track features electrifying music by Sachin-Jigar, soulful vocals by Rashmeet Kaur & Rana Majumdar, and powerful lyrics penned by Amitabh Bhattacharya.

In Cinemas 11th July 2025

Stay updated with the latest videos from Tips Official. Subscribe on the link below.
http://youtube.com/tipsofficial

snippet.title: Kannappa Movie Making | A Grand Cinematic Journey Begins | Vishnu Manchu | Mohan Babu | Prabhas |AVA
snippet.description:
Step behind the scenes of Kannappa, the much-awaited epic saga starring Vishnu Manchu, and witness the making of this visual spectacle!

From elaborate sets to intense action sequences, this making video showcases the passion, effort, and vision that brought the timeless legend of Kannappa to life.

üî± Kannappa ‚Äì Releasing Worldwide on 27th June 2025!

‚ú® CAST & CREW:

Starring: Vishnu Manchu, Mohan Babu, Prabhas, Mohanlal, Akshay Kumar, Sarat Kumar, Kajal Aggarwal, Arpit Ranka, Brahmanandam, Saptagiri, Mukesh Rishi, Madhubala, Aishwarya Bhaskaran, Brahmaji, Devaraj, Raghu Babu, Siva Balaji, Sampath Ram, Lavi Pajni, Surekha Vani, Preity Mukundhan, Kaushal And Adhurs Raghu.

Story & Screenplay: Vishnu Manchu
Producer: Dr.M. Mohan Babu
Banner: Twenty Four Frames Factory & AVA Entertainment
Director: Mukhesh Kumar Singh
Cinematographer: Sheldon Chau
Music Director: Stephen Devassy
Editor: Anthony Gonsalvez
Production Designer: Chinna
Executive Producer: Vinay Maheshwari & R.Vijay Kumar
Stunts Master: Kecha Khamphakdee
Choreography: Prabhudeva, Brinda & Ganesh
PRO: Haswath Saravanan & Sai Satish
DI & Sound Mixing: Annapurna Studios

Music Label: T-Series

Some scientists claim to have captured a strange glowing phenomenon, something like an aura emerging from the human body using their instruments. You might‚Äôve seen viral reports on the internet suggesting this too. But what exactly is this mysterious light that appears in living beings but vanishes after death and that isn‚Äôt just body heat?

This very question intrigued a brilliant Japanese scientist, Masaki Kobayashi from Tohoku University, back in 2009. To find the answer, he conducted a groundbreaking experiment on this so-called ‚Äúhuman light‚Äù. Little did he know, his discovery would shake the way we perceive reality.

Interestingly, many scientists at the time believed no scientific evidence could ever prove the existence of a soul or consciousness and they conducted experiments to support that view. But Masaki wasn‚Äôt fully convinced. What did he know about this mysterious light that others didn‚Äôt? So, was Masaki Kobayashi just measuring light, or was he witnessing something far deeper?
Is this strange glow just a biological glitch, or the first glimpse of the human soul?
And if something truly leaves the body when we die, what exactly are we?

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

snippet.title: GAANJI - Official Music Video | Chandan Shetty | Folk x Fusion
snippet.description:
From North Karnataka to the World: A Folk Song Reimagined Through Dance. Having zero expectations and a full heart, I present to you this experimental music video ‚Äî a piece of art born from a deeply personal journey.

I composed this song nine years ago, inspired by a beloved folk rhyme from North Karnataka. Over time, its melody stayed close to me, quietly asking to be brought to life in a new form.

The visual inspiration comes from a range of minimalistic music videos, especially those shot on white-screen backgrounds (like ‚ÄòSorry‚Äô from Justin Bieber). I finally started working on the video in 2023, and just two months ago, we brought it to life.

We held virtual auditions across India, and with the brilliant support of choreographers Praveen Veigas,  Pushpa, and Muskan, we selected 10 incredible dancers who brought their energy and magic to this performance.

This project would not have been possible without the dedication and brilliance of a phenomenal team:
        ‚Ä¢        Co-Producer: Greeshma Gowda
        ‚Ä¢        DOP: Suhas Amin
        ‚Ä¢        Editor & VFX: Dheeraj Poojary
        ‚Ä¢        Programming, Mixing & Mastering: Agastya Raag
        ‚Ä¢       Dancers: Alina Khan, Yukta, Muskan, Chaitanya, Payal, Jaquline, Sana, Shivani, Sneha.
        ‚Ä¢       Chorus: Mahalakshmi, Harismaran . A, Harshit N.U, Siri B.S, Prerana Navalgi, Nikisha H.A, Sana .S, Meghana Saishree, Shivani .S, Kshama .D Raj, Sanchita Vinay, M. Madhumitha, Dhriti Vishwanath, Isha .V, Omkar Kumble, Ghanashyam G.R, Tanav .S, Arav G.A, Ruchitha .V, Ridhima .K, Pranathi .V, Panvi N.U.
        ‚Ä¢      Poster Design : Ankith Anil 
        ‚Ä¢      Digitally Distributed by A3 Labels
        ‚Ä¢      Digital Promotions: Digital Magnet Media - Dhanu Krishnaa


To all the technicians and artists involved ‚Äî your work has been outstanding, and I deeply appreciate each one of you.

This video is directed by Chandan Shetty, and represents not just a song, but a dream nurtured over time.

I truly hope you connect with it, feel the spirit behind it, and show it some love.

Listen on your favorite platform: 
Spotify:https://open.spotify.com/track/0nTl1C6WCW2yv5P2G8eK87?si=07abf20415544345
Jio Saavn:https://www.jiosaavn.com/song/gaanji/Oxwgfyd0VXI
Youtube Music:https://music.youtube.com/watch?v=RUtZl_J0uqs&si=i8lDF-NJKb6_S07W
Amazon Music:https://music.amazon.in/tracks/B0FDLBF9XT?marketplaceId=A21TJRUUN4KGV&musicTerritory=IN&ref=dm_sh_HDPV6NH03U4CakUQzl0UUvf2A
iTunes:https://music.apple.com/us/song/gaanji/1821465090
Apple Music:https://music.apple.com/us/song/gaanji/1821465090
Gaana:https://gaana.com/song/gaanji
Instagram:https://www.instagram.com/reels/audio/1395192328197759/
